#+COMMENT:                                                            -*- org -*-
#+TITLE: Hacking Dezyne command line tools

* Regression test

    make check

Run an individual test

   ./pre-inst-env run test/all/hello

Re-run all failures (e.g., after making fixes)

    make recheck

Run all parser tests

    make check FULL_TESTS="$(cd test/parser; ls -1)"

Run all verification failure tests

    make check FULL_TESTS="$(cd test/error; ls -1)"

* GNU/Linux binary pack (generic, relocatable)

    guix environment -l guix.scm

    git clean -fdx

    git describe                           # input for version and sha256 field of
    guix hash -rx .

    edit guix/gnu/packages/dzn.scm         # dzn package to update
    git commit -am 'release: v2.9.0-287'
    git push buildmaster                   # push your commit/branch for dzn to find

    ./autogen.sh                           # updates version
    ./configure

    make
    GUIX_PACKAGE_PATH=guix guix build dzn  # offloaded dzn package build
    make linux                             # non-offloaded pack (to avoid network load)

* MinGW cross build

Try something like

    guix environment -l mingw.scm --pure --ad-hoc guix

    guile="$(GUIX_PACKAGE_PATH=guix guix build --target=x86_64-w64-mingw32 guile-mingw | grep -v debug)"
    export PKG_CONFIG_PATH="$guile/lib/pkgconfig"
    export GUILE_TOOLS=$GUIX_ENVIRONMENT/bin/guild
    ./configure --host=x86_64-w64-mingw32
    make GUILE_TOOLS=$GUILE_TOOLS

